  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN135.1-kilavi"><app><lem>piriviṉkaṇ</lem><rdg wit="#C7 #RK">talaimakaṉ piriviṉkaṇ</rdg></app> vēṟupaṭṭa talaimaka ṭōḻikkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What SHE, who had undergone changes during the separation, said to the confidante.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN135.1">
                <l>titalai māmai taḷirvaṉap paḻukaip</l>
                <l>putalivar pīri ṉetirmalar kaṭuppap</l>
                <l>pacalai pāynta nutalē ṉāki</l>
                <l>yeḻuteḻiṉ maḻaikkaṇ kaluḻa nōykūrn</l>
                <l>tāti mantiyi ṉaṟivupiṟi tākip</l>
                <l>pētuṟ ṟiciṉē kātalan tōḻi</l>
                <l>kāykatir tirukaliṟ kaṉaintukāl kaṭuki</l>
                <l>yāṭutaḷi <supplied>ri</supplied>ruppaik kūṭukuvi vāṉpūk</l>
                <l>kōṭukaṭai kaḻaṅki ṉaṟaimicait tāaṅ</l>
                <l>kāṭiṟan taṉarē kātala raṭupōr</l>
                <l><supplied>vī</supplied>yā viḻuppukaḻ viṇṭōy viyaṉkuṭai</l>
                <l>yīreḻu vēḷi ri<supplied>yai</supplied>ntoruṅ keṟinta</l>
                <l>kaḻuvuḷ kāmukar pōlak</l>
                <l>kalakkiṉṟu mātavart teḷintave ṉeñcē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Being one with a forehead where pallor has spread</l>
                <l>so as to resemble the future blossoms of the sponge-gourd, creeping over bushes,</l>
                <l>[pallor that is a] lament for [my] beauty spots, dark complexion [and] sprout[-like] beauty, (1-3)</l>
                <l>filled with pain so that [my] painted graceful rain eyes dim, (4)</l>
                <l>[my] awareness becoming different, like [that of] Ātimanti, (5)</l>
                <l>let me experience folly, beloved friend. (6)</l>
                <l>[His] feet very much in haste, because of being wrung by hot [sun] rays, (7)</l>
                <l>[our] lover has gone to traverse the wilderness, (10a-c)</l>
                <l>where the pure flowers combined in heaps of the Mahua tree with swaying sprouts</l>
                <l>spread on the rocks, like molucca beans with rims that are curved. (8f.)</l>
                <l>Like the courtiers of Kaḻuvuḷ, (13)</l>
                <l>with unperishing excellent fame on the battlefield [and] a sky-touching wide parasol,</l>
                <l>who was attacked by an alliance of twice seven Vēḷir, (11f.)</l>
                <l>is not my heart that trusted him very upset? (14)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
